        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3674262709" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14545147665068742484">4 1/2 stars<br/><br/>I love Toni Morrison books and this one, “Sula” was exceptional like most of the others I’ve read. <br/><br/>Typical of most of Toni Morrison’s books, the writing was outstanding in every way. Descriptions were so clear and so vibrant that one could taste flavors and feel the emotions. That is Toni Morrison at her best!<br/><br/>Pacing was outstanding. It started quickly, although I will admit, I got a little bit lost in the middle but it finished very strongly.<br/><br/>Part of why I love Morrison is that she doe</span>
  <span id="freeText14545147665068742484" style="display:none">4 1/2 stars<br /><br />I love Toni Morrison books and this one, “Sula” was exceptional like most of the others I’ve read. <br /><br />Typical of most of Toni Morrison’s books, the writing was outstanding in every way. Descriptions were so clear and so vibrant that one could taste flavors and feel the emotions. That is Toni Morrison at her best!<br /><br />Pacing was outstanding. It started quickly, although I will admit, I got a little bit lost in the middle but it finished very strongly.<br /><br />Part of why I love Morrison is that she doesn’t back away from controversy. This book is exceptional in that respect. <br /><br />I highly recommend this book.</span>
